How does one line of Spark code become work across a whole cluster? Follow it down.

It starts with the driver. The driver reads your code and builds a plan.

That plan is a directed acyclic graph, a dag. It maps every transformation in dependency order.

Spark slices that map into stages. A stage is work that runs without shuffling data over the network, so here the plan splits in two.

Each stage becomes tasks, with one task per partition of data. And those tasks drop onto the executors, the workers that run them in parallel.

That's how a single command turns into work flowing across many machines.
